OL,3,CWales Debate: Devolution thrust to
OL,4,Ccentre of UK election campaigns
OL,6,FLabour's Jo Stevens used her time in
OL,7,Fthe debate to make the point that
OL,8,Fthere would be an "immediate cash
OL,9,Finjection" for the NHS in Wales from a
OL,10,FLabour UK Government and, while she
OL,11,Fwouldn't be drawn when I asked her if
OL,12,FKeir Starmer would insist that Vaughan
OL,13,FGething passed on that money, she did
OL,14,Fsay that Welsh Labour leaders had
OL,15,Fsigned off the manifesto and would
OL,16,Fwant to align itself with the UK
OL,17,FGovernment plans.
OL,19,FNow, this is where, for me, questions
OL,20,Fbegin to emerge about how two Labour
OL,21,Fgovernments would work together.
